claims:
1. A method to implement a diversity sampler process to select new batches of unlabeled instances, comprising:
by one or more computing devices:
obtaining a current version of a classification model M, an unlabeled set of available documents D, and a cosine similarity threshold t;
sorting the unlabeled set of available documents D based on each of the documents absolute distance from the current version of the classification model M to obtain sorted indices I for each document of the unlabeled set of available documents D;
inserting the sorted document, of the sorted unlabeled set of available documents D, having a nearest sorted index I[1] from the current version of the classification model M into a new batch of unlabeled instances Bc;
obtaining sorted indices I of the sorted unlabeled set of available documents D that have a cosine angle ≥t with respect to the inserted document I[1];
removing the documents with the obtained sorted indices I from the sorted unlabeled set of available documents D; and
repeating the insert operation, the second obtain operation, and the remove operation until the new batch of unlabeled instances Bc are selected.
2. The method of claim 1, wherein the classification model M is a hyperplane.
3. The method of claim 1, wherein the unlabeled set of available documents D are sorted in increasing order.
4. The method of claim 1, wherein, in the first obtaining step, the one or more computing devises further obtains a batch size k.
5. The method of claim 4, wherein the one or more computing devises performs the steps of repeating the insert operation, the second obtain operation, and the remove operation until k documents are inserted into the new batch of unlabeled instances Bc.
6. The method of claim 1, wherein the Diversity Sampler process is implemented using a support vector machine (SVM).
7. The method of claim 1, wherein the Diversity Sampler process is implemented in a technology-assisted document review.
8. The method of claim 1, wherein the current version of the classification model M is created by:
obtaining an unlabeled set of documents D;
obtaining a batch size k;
constructing a first batch of k documents D;
obtaining labels for the first batch of k documents D, wherein the labeled first batch of k documents D are referred to as training data documents; and
constructing the current version of the classification model M using the training documents.
9. The method of claim 8, further comprising:
obtaining labels for the new batch of unlabeled instances Bc; and
adding the labeled new batch of instances Bc to a current version of the training data documents referred to as extended training data documents Dc.
10. The method of claim 9, further comprising constructing an updated classification model M using the extended training data documents Dc.
